public static EPlusMaterial.SimpleGlazing setSimpleGlazing(java.lang.String name,
                                                           Param U,
                                                           Param SHGC,
                                                           Param visibleTransmittance)
define a green roof material according to its physical properties and the plant properties example Material:RoofVegetation, BaseEco, !- Name 0.5, !- Height of Plants {m} 5, !- Leaf Area Index {dimensionless} 0.2, !- Leaf Reflectivity {dimensionless} 0.95, !- Leaf Emissivity 180, !- Minimum Stomatal Resistance (s/m) EcoRoofSoil, !- Soil Layer Name MediumSmooth, !- Roughness 0.18, !- Thickness {m} 0.4, !- Conductivity (dry soil) {W/m-K} 641, !- Density (dry soil) {kg/m3} 1100, !- Specific Heat (dry soil) {J/kg-K} 0.95, !- Thermal Absorptance 0.8, !- Solar Absorptance 0.7, !- Visible Absorptance 0.4, !- Max volumetric moisture content of the soil layer (saturation) 0.01, !- Min (residual) volumetric moisture content of the soil layer 0.2; !- Initial volumetric moisture content of the soil layer BaseEco, !- Name

Parameters:
plantheight -
leafAreaIndex -
leafReflectivity -
leafEmissivity -
minStomataR -
soilMaterial -
roughness - - material roughness scale from 0 (very rough) to 5 (very smooth)
thick - - material thickness
k - - material thermal conductivity
rho - - material density
C - - material specific heat
thermalAbsorptance - - fraction of incident long wavelength radiation absorbed by the material [0..1]
solarAbsorptance - - fraction of incident solar radiation absorbed by the material [0..1]
visibleAbsorptance - - fraction of visible light absorbed by the material [0..1]
